page.title: 05Wildlife LISVANE
page.content: The varied countryside gives a wide range of habitats.These are some of the things seen in 1985. {MAMMELS}-Fox,Brown Rat,Bank Vole,Grey Squirrel,Hedgehog,Mole and Rabbit. {AMPHIBIANS}-Common Newt,Frog,Toad. {REPTILES}-Adder,Grass Snake,Sloworm and Common Lizard. {INVERTABRATES}-a wide range-included spiders,centipedes,flies,wasps and bees. Butterflies included Orange Tip, Large White,Brimstone and Peacock. {BIRDS -(i)}Resident:includes Collared Dove,Tawny Owl,Buzzard,Kestrel, Greenfinch,Meadow Pipit,Blue,Great, Coal,Long Tailed Tits. {(ii)}Winter:Redwing,Fieldfare,Siskin. {(iii)}Summer:Swift,Swallow,House Martin,Willow Warber,Chiff Chaff, Cuckoo.{(iv)}Regular passage mirgrants :Pied Flycatcher,Redstart,Wheatear.
